               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16880531-14-off71-c61" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880531-14-defend84 t16880531-14-off71 t16880531-14-verdict73"></join>
         
               <p>Middlesex Side. 
               
                  <persName id="t16880531-14-defend84" type="defendantName">
                     Simon 
                     How
                  <interp inst="t16880531-14-defend84" type="surname" value="How"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880531-14-defend84" type="given" value="Simon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880531-14-defend84" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , of the Parish of <placeName id="t16880531-14-defloc70">Stepney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16880531-14-defloc70" type="placeName" value="Stepney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16880531-14-defloc70" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880531-14-defend84 t16880531-14-defloc70"></join>, in the County of Middlesex, was Indicted for <rs id="t16880531-14-off71" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16880531-14-off71" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880531-14-off71" type="offenceSubcategory" value="other"></interp>
               Runing from his Colours, he being entertained as a Soldier in the Regiment of the Right Honourable the Lord Dartmouth; in which Regiment he continued for about the space of two Years and upward, and Received the Kingspay
            </rs>; But in February last sented himself, and was taken in Rosemary Lane, The Prisoner did not deny his going away,  said he was poor, and had Money oweing him  f the Company,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="16880531003"></xptr>he being a <rs id="t16880531-14-deflabel72" type="occupation">Suttler, or Seller of drink</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880531-14-defend84 t16880531-14-deflabel72"></join> to them. So upon the whole, the Evidence being plain against him that he Received the Kings pay, though not positive of his Receiving the Press Money he was found <rs id="t16880531-14-verdict73" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16880531-14-verdict73" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>, &amp;c.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16880531-14-punish74" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16880531-14-punish74" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880531-14-defend84 t16880531-14-punish74"></join>
               
                     <note>[Death. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
